UNITED STATES of America ex rel. Vincenzo FERRERO, Relator-Appellant, v. COMMISSIONER OF IMMIGRATION, Ellis Island, New York Harbor, Respondent-Appellee.* No. 103. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 2, 1936. Carol King, of New York City (Isaac Shorr, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Lamar Hardy, U. S. Atty., of New York City (William F. Young, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

Writ of certiorari denied 57 S. Ct. 431, 81 L. Ed. —.

 PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
